VPC Peering
What is VPC Peering?

VPC Peering is a connection between two VPCs that allows them to communicate with each other using private IP addresses.

Simple Definition

VPC Peering connects two VPCs so they can communicate securely using private IPs.



Why Do We Use VPC Peering?

Connect two VPCs securely.
Share resources between VPCs.
Communication happens using private IP addresses.
No need to use the public internet.

How It Works
      VPC-A                     VPC-B
  10.0.0.0/16              192.168.0.0/16
       │                         │
       └────── VPC Peering ──────┘
                 │
        Private Communication

Easy Way to Remember

VPC Peering = Private Bridge Between Two VPCs

Just like a bridge connects two islands, VPC Peering connects two VPCs so they can communicate privately without using the internet.


Requirements

Both VPCs must have different (non-overlapping) CIDR blocks.
Update the Route Tables in both VPCs.
Accept the VPC Peering request.

Advantages

Secure communication
Low network latency
Uses private IP addresses
No internet required
